This paper focuses on the optimization of neural network architectures for a specific target device, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a differentiable Neural Architecture Search (NAS) method also falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of energy consumption, which is relevant to the field of robotics and control systems (cs.AR, cs.SY).
